In the enforcement of this Part VII, the administrative clerk to the zoning board or the administrator of the County Council, as appropriate, considering an application shall be subject to the authority of the Howard County Ethics Commission and, unless otherwise directed by the Ethics Commission, shall:
receive filings of affidavits and disclosures;
maintain filed affidavits and disclosures as public records available for review by the general public during normal business hours;
report violations to the Howard County Ethics Commission; and
perform ministerial duties necessary to administer this Part VII.
